				<p class="paragraph--2">"<em>In the past, we relied heavily on scheduled remote scans to identify vulnerabilities,</em>" says Monga. "<em>However, one challenge was that some of our clinics completely power down their systems at the end of the working day, so we'd miss them if automated scans were triggered in the early morning hours. Our scans would also conflict with our production systems, which meant we could only scan some assets once a month.</em>"</p>

